<subSubSection id="CC27B4720133A4DCFD62AB7F0ECF298E" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="material examined">
<paragraph id="433D6DE79CDB743C576A8D55A1D1AD2A" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="66824AD72E73A3A011F79AF9B7C0BE8B" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Schizoholotype (2 slides, one with dissociated spicules, the other with section at right angles to surface): NHM collection, Bwbk. 542 (labeled as 
<taxonomicName id="F8055C672F7B637B2E949107FCD9698C" authority="Bowerbank, 1874" authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1874" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Battersbyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Battersbyia bucklandi" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bucklandi">Battersbyia bucklandi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1138AECECE078721DDB2CAC2CAB0EA80" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondriidae" genus="Hymeniacidon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hymeniacidon bucklandi" order="Suberitida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bucklandi">Hymeniacidon bucklandi</taxonomicName>
), part of holotype BMNH 1877.5.21.142 (wet, fragment examined); locality presumed to be Abbey Bay, near Torquay, Devon, England (but this is not indicated on the labels).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD9D75E8E6B056AB4734A115F3982F1B" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
